<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>New password</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter a new password to give the user account this password.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Repeat password</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">Enter the password again.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>New app PIN</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock">For users that operate the plentymarkets app, you can enter a PIN with between 4 and 12 numbers to activate this user for quick account switching. If you save a PIN, users can quickly be switched in the plentymarkets app. However, the user can also log into the plentymarkets app using their password.<br>
<strong><em>Tipp:</em></strong> After the PIN is saved, the field contains 4 dots. These dots show that an app PIN has been saved for the user account. The actual PIN might consist of more numbers.<br>
When switching users, any user account for which a PIN has been saved can be selected. To remove the PIN, e.g. because the user no longer works with the app, delete the 4 dots and save the user account.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Repeat app PIN</strong></p></td>
